Sentencas: Creep rupture is investigated at 800 degrees C of a joint between a glass-ceramic sealant and a ferritic stainless steel interconnect coated with lanthanum strontium manganite for solid oxide fuel cell application.
Titulo: Creep rupture of the joint between a glass-ceramic sealant and lanthanum strontium manganite-coated ferritic stainless steel interconnect for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results reveal the shear and tensile creep strength of the as-joined, non-aged joint at a rupture time of 1000 h is about 42% and 3% of the average shear and tensile bonding strength, respectively.
Titulo: Creep rupture of the joint between a glass-ceramic sealant and lanthanum strontium manganite-coated ferritic stainless steel interconnect for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A thermal aging of 1000 h at 800 degrees C enhances the creep strength.
Titulo: Creep rupture of the joint between a glass-ceramic sealant and lanthanum strontium manganite-coated ferritic stainless steel interconnect for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For both non-aged shear and tensile specimens with a short creep rupture time, fracture mainly takes place in an oxyapatite interlayer which is formed in the joining process.
Titulo: Creep rupture of the joint between a glass-ceramic sealant and lanthanum strontium manganite-coated ferritic stainless steel interconnect for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For a medium creep rupture time, fracture site changes to a mixed BaCrO4/oxyapatite layer.
Titulo: Creep rupture of the joint between a glass-ceramic sealant and lanthanum strontium manganite-coated ferritic stainless steel interconnect for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Oxyapatite and BaCrO4 dominate the creep failure mechanism for 1000 h-aged shear specimens, while (Cr,Mn)(3)O-4 spine] plays a role in the creep failure of 1000 h aged tensile specimens.
Titulo: Creep rupture of the joint between a glass-ceramic sealant and lanthanum strontium manganite-coated ferritic stainless steel interconnect for solid oxide fuel cells
